data.title: First Timer and Hit it out of the Park
data.text: My wife and I walked by on a whim and grabbed a couple of wraps and falafel to go.  The interior is really nice and polished for a [sort of] hole in the wall establishment.  We were blown away by their food.  Excellent wraps, pretty sizable for Mediterranean style and the falafel were some of the best we have tasted.  We found our new go-to for shwarma wraps!

data.title: Great food and good service
data.text: Jordanian food, typical middle eastern fare that is done right. The bread like pita and lavash is baked fresh and makes a big difference. I like the falafel and typically order that or the shawarma . The owner and his staff go the extra mile to take care of customers and that means a lot. I will say my only negative would be putting lettuce in my falafel pita which is a no no.

data.title: A new place for baklava!
data.text: My son and I visited for a Saturday afternoon meal - very fun and interesting menu. I hope they are around for a long time! Baklava was yummy.
